+# Curator Log - exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall / step-002 / curator-002
+
+## Inputs
+
+- Report:
+  `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/library-inbox/step-002-exploration-002-recursive-closure-and-spillover-audit.md`
+- Meta note:
+  `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/meta-inbox/meta-step-002-exploration-002.md`
+
+## Atomic Findings Extracted
+
+1. At the one-triad Step-2 budget, every honest canonical seed spills outside
+   the budget on the first honest recursive-closure pass once mandatory
+   conjugate completion is enforced.
+2. The first closure-forced off-orbit wavevectors are already visible on the
+   mirror-complete ledger, at minimum
+   `plus/minus (p - q)`,
+   `plus/minus (2p + q)`,
+   and
+   `plus/minus (p + 2q)`.
+3. The decisive first spill comes from distinct off-orbit pairs created by
+   conjugate completion, not from same-wavevector self-pairs, because the
+   Step-1 exact interaction scalar kills the self-doubling term by
+   divergence-free orthogonality.
+4. This is a current-budget negative only: the report earns failure of the
+   frozen one-triad budget, not a theorem that the closure tower is infinite.
+5. The reusable meta lesson is that exact-support audits should test
+   mirror-cross pairs on the full conjugate-complete ledger before reasoning
+   from a tidy intended orbit or from vanished self-pair doubling.
+
+## Filing Decisions
+
+- Added factual entry:
+  `library/factual/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/canonical-one-triad-seeds-spill-outside-the-first-budget-on-the-first-honest-closure-pass.md`
